docs.abstract: The Black Music Action Coalition issued a 37-page report examining if powerful companies followed through on diversity commitments made last summer.
docs.snippet: The Black Music Action Coalition issued a 37-page report examining if powerful companies followed through on diversity commitments made last summer.
docs.lead_paragraph: A new “report card” on race in the music business takes many of the industry’s most powerful companies to task, urging them to follow through on diversity commitments made last summer amid nationwide protests over the murder of George Floyd.

headline.main: A Race ‘Report Card’ Measures Whether the Music Industry Changed

docs.abstract: The officers face criminal prosecution for responses to demonstrations last year that Mayor Andrew Ginther said “did not meet my expectations or the community’s.”
docs.snippet: The officers face criminal prosecution for responses to demonstrations last year that Mayor Andrew Ginther said “did not meet my expectations or the community’s.”
docs.lead_paragraph: Three police officers in Columbus, Ohio, face criminal charges for their conduct during protests over the death of George Floyd last year, when officers in cities across the United States frequently used force to break up demonstrations.

headline.main: 3 Columbus Officers Are Charged With Misconduct in George Floyd Protests

docs.abstract: Thomas Lane, J. Alexander Kueng and Tou Thao were originally set to stand trial together in August, but after Mr. Chauvin’s conviction, the judge ruled that the second trial would be held in March to put some “space” between them.
docs.snippet: Thomas Lane, J. Alexander Kueng and Tou Thao were originally set to stand trial together in August, but after Mr. Chauvin’s conviction, the judge ruled that the second trial would be held in March to put some “space” between them.
docs.lead_paragraph: MINNEAPOLIS — The sentencing of Derek Chauvin to 22 and a half years in prison for the second-degree murder of George Floyd will bring a measure of closure to a case that has deeply traumatized the Twin Cities and set off mass protests across the nation.

headline.main: Three other officers on the scene with Derek Chauvin still face their own charges.

docs.abstract: The indictment came more than a year after the fatal shooting. The family of the victim protested the charges as too lenient, calling them “unjust” and “unacceptable.”

docs.lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — A police officer who fatally shot an unarmed Palestinian man with autism was charged with manslaughter on Thursday, in a case that brought attention to the issue of police brutality.

headline.main: Israeli Officer Who Killed Autistic Palestinian Man Charged With Manslaughter
headline.print_headline: Manslaughter Charge for Israeli Policeman  Who Shot Palestinian Man Who Had Autism

docs.abstract: Matthew A. Frank asked the judge to sentence Derek Chauvin to 30 years in prison.
docs.snippet: Matthew A. Frank asked the judge to sentence Derek Chauvin to 30 years in prison.
docs.lead_paragraph: Asking a judge to sentence Derek Chauvin to three decades in prison for killing George Floyd, a prosecutor said Mr. Chauvin had carried out “nine and a half minutes of cruelty” when he knelt on Mr. Floyd’s neck as he took his last breaths.

headline.main: Urging a long prison sentence, a prosecutor says Derek Chauvin carried out ‘9 and a half minutes of cruelty.’

docs.abstract: In this stylish documentary, young men discuss their country’s laws criminalizing gay sex.
docs.snippet: In this stylish documentary, young men discuss their country’s laws criminalizing gay sex.
docs.lead_paragraph: The documentary “The Legend of the Underground” captures queer Nigerian activists as they discuss their country’s laws criminalizing gay sex. Together, they lament unjust arrests and police brutality. But they are not aiming for either martyrdom or altruism — instead, their goal is to improve the circumstances of their own lives.

headline.main: ‘The Legend of the Underground’ Review: Gay Activism in Nigeria

docs.abstract: The annual awards recognized journalism on the murder of George Floyd, including a special citation for Darnella Frazier, the teenager who filmed the killing. The public service prize went to The New York Times for Covid coverage.
docs.snippet: The annual awards recognized journalism on the murder of George Floyd, including a special citation for Darnella Frazier, the teenager who filmed the killing. The public service prize went to The New York Times for Covid coverage.
docs.lead_paragraph: Pulitzer Prizes were awarded on Friday to news organizations that provided in-depth coverage of the dramatic turns of 2020, a year dominated by a pandemic that left millions dead and a national conversation on race after the murder of George Floyd.

headline.main: Pulitzer Prizes Focus on Coverage of Pandemic and Law Enforcement

docs.abstract: Since the murder of George Floyd, the racial justice movement has received millions of dollars in donations. But some chapters have questioned how those funds are spent.
docs.snippet: Since the murder of George Floyd, the racial justice movement has received millions of dollars in donations. But some chapters have questioned how those funds are spent.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the year since George Floyd was murdered, racial justice organizations across the country have been inundated with millions of dollars in donations and thousands of eager new activists. They have earned a prominent platform that puts them on the front lines of political and social battles.

headline.main: Black Lives Matter Has Grown More Powerful, and More Divided
headline.print_headline: Tensions Rise As Movement Makes Strides

docs.abstract: The magazine’s Ethicist columnist on whether it’s hypocritical for a liberal to socialize with an increasingly extreme conservative.
docs.snippet: The magazine’s Ethicist columnist on whether it’s hypocritical for a liberal to socialize with an increasingly extreme conservative.
docs.lead_paragraph: I am a liberal in a blue city in a red state. One of my friends is married to a man who has become increasingly conservative over the past year (an “anti-Black Lives Matter, anti-abortion, Democrats are all idiots and socialists are taking over the country” mind-set), and his posts on social media are becoming more and more extreme. We occasionally socialize as couples. When we are together, I am friendly with him, and we avoid overt political talk, but as his social media becomes more and more extreme, I feel conflicted about continuing to accept invitations to socialize with them. Is it hypocritical of me to socialize with them when I find his personal political views so abhorrent? Name Withheld.

headline.main: Should I Hang Out With Someone Whose Political Views I Hate?
headline.print_headline: Should I Hang Out With Someone Whose Political Views I Hate?
